import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import pylab
import scipy.stats
import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm

from statsmodels.stats.outliers_influence import OLSInfluence
from scipy import stats

%matplotlib inline
sns.set()

class Regression_Data:
    
    set1 = pd.DataFrame()
    set2 = pd.DataFrame()
    set3 = pd.DataFrame()
    set4 = pd.DataFrame()
    set5 = pd.DataFrame()
    set6 = pd.DataFrame()
    
    def load_file(self, file_name):
        
        self.set1 = pd.read_excel(file_name, sheet_name = 'Set 1')
        self.set2 = pd.read_excel(file_name, sheet_name = 'Set 2')
        self.set3 = pd.read_excel(file_name, sheet_name = 'Set 3')
        self.set4 = pd.read_excel(file_name, sheet_name = 'Set 4')
        self.set5 = pd.read_excel(file_name, sheet_name = 'Set 5')
        self.set6 = pd.read_excel(file_name, sheet_name = 'Set 6')
        
        self.set3['y_sqrt'] = np.sqrt(self.set3['y'])
        self.set3['y_log'] = np.log(self.set3['y'])
        self.set4['y_log'] = np.log(self.set4['y'])
    
    def coefficient_confidence(self, data_set, transform):
    
        coefficients_list = []

        for count in range(1, 10000):
            index = range(0, len(data_set))
            index_bootstrap = np.random.choice(index, len(index), replace = True)
            set_bootstrap = data_set.iloc[index_bootstrap]
            X = sm.add_constant(set_bootstrap.x)
            y = set_bootstrap.y
            
            if transform == 'log': y = set_bootstrap.y_log
            elif transform == 'sqrt': y = set_bootstrap.y_sqrt

            model = sm.OLS(y, X)
            results = model.fit()
            coefficients_list.append(results.params[1])

        print('Confidence interval at 90% confidence:', stats.t.interval(alpha = .9, 
                             df = (len(coefficients_list) - 1), 
                             loc = np.mean(coefficients_list), 
                             scale = stats.sem(coefficients_list)))
    
    def __init__(self):
        
        pass
        
_regression_data = Regression_Data()
_regression_data.load_file('linear_regression_data.xlsx')

deltas = []

slope = parameters[1]
intercept = parameters[0]

set3_sqrt = _regression_data.set3.loc[:,['y_sqrt', 'x']]
